mint-mechanic (0.8.0) noble; urgency=medium

  * Add a live-session layer to the removal guard. Alongside the static list of
    known desktops, it now detects the desktop session and login manager that
    are actually running on this machine and refuses to remove the packages they
    depend on. An exotic desktop the built-in list never named is still
    protected, because it is the one drawing the screen.
  * The layer is purely additive: a detection miss falls back to the static
    list, so it can only ever refuse more, never less. Graphics drivers are left
    to the static list on purpose, since the in-use driver is often a DKMS
    module dpkg does not own.

 -- Ron Craig (rclinux) <rcraig.netmail@gmail.com>  Sun, 19 Jul 2026 16:20:04 -0400

mint-mechanic (0.7.0) noble; urgency=medium

  * Widen the removal guard beyond Cinnamon: it now refuses removals that would
    take a MATE, XFCE, KDE Plasma, GNOME, Budgie or LXQt session, or any of the
    display managers, with them.
  * Protect the graphics libraries the old guard missed. Matching a "mesa-"
    prefix caught mesa-utils, a diagnostic tool, while missing libgl1-mesa-dri
    and libglx-mesa0 - the actual drivers.
  * Match desktop components by exact name rather than a broad prefix, so
    ordinary packages stay removable. A "mate-" prefix would have covered all 68
    mate-* packages including mate-calc; refusing to uninstall a calculator
    teaches users to ignore the guard.

 -- Ron Craig (rclinux) <rcraig.netmail@gmail.com>  Sun, 19 Jul 2026 11:07:11 -0400

mint-mechanic (0.6.0) noble; urgency=medium

  * Wrap long text in task descriptions and status lines instead of clipping it
    at the right edge. This mattered beyond appearance: the status line carries
    the removal-refusal messages, so a truncated line could hide why an
    operation was refused.
  * Fix the cleaner status reading "Nothing done.  Done - re-measured." when the
    orphan step was the only task selected.

 -- Ron Craig (rclinux) <rcraig.netmail@gmail.com>  Sun, 19 Jul 2026 10:58:34 -0400

mint-mechanic (0.5.0) noble; urgency=medium

  * Publish to ppa:rclinux/mint-mechanic so updates reach users through the
    normal apt update path. Previous releases were download-only, which meant
    security fixes could not reach anyone who had already installed.
  * Add AppStream metainfo so the application lists in software centres.
  * Convert packaging to a debhelper source package; debian/ is now the single
    source of packaging truth and build-deb.sh delegates to it.
  * Add build-source.sh for producing signed source uploads.
  * Add tests asserting the app version, changelog, man page, README and
    AppStream metadata never disagree.

 -- Ron Craig (rclinux) <rcraig.netmail@gmail.com>  Sun, 19 Jul 2026 09:25:53 -0400

mint-mechanic (0.4.0) noble; urgency=medium

  * Uninstaller: preview APT's real removal cascade and require confirmation;
    refuse selections that would remove session-critical packages.
  * Move the removal preview/guard into ltt/pkg.py so the Cleaner and the
    Uninstaller share one implementation and cannot diverge.

 -- Ron Craig (rclinux) <rcraig.netmail@gmail.com>  Sun, 19 Jul 2026 08:03:07 -0400
